'''James Adamson''' (born 1920s) was a [[Scotland|Scottish]] professional [[Football (soccer)|footballer]] who played as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]]. Adamson was playing as a seventeen-year-old for junior side [[Dundee Violet F.C.|Dundee Violet]] when he signed for [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]] in August 1944. Playing ten times that season, Adamson was loaned out to [[Brechin City F.C.|Brechin City]] the following season and was called up for [[Military service#United Kingdom|military service]] before being released in April 1947.<ref>{{cite book|last=Gracie|first=Steve|title=A Passion For Survival|publisher=[[Arabest Publishing Dundee]]|year=2008|isbn=978-0-9558341-0-3}}</ref> It is unknown where he went after this.
