'''Vasily Sergeyevich Smirnov''' ({{lang-ru|Васи́лий Серге́евич Смирно́в}}; born December 20, 1914 O.S./January 2, 1915 N.S. in [[Saint Petersburg|Petrograd]]; died March 5, 1973 in Leningrad) was a [[Russians|Russian]] [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] [[metallurgy|metallurgist]] and a corresponding member of the [[Russian Academy of Sciences|Soviet Academy of Sciences]] (since 1960). He made notable contributions to understanding the [[Deformation (engineering)#Plastic deformation|plastic deformation]] process.

